parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of an engine cylinder can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine blows a hole through the casting
damaging the inner axle shaft carrier bearing
causing the vehicle to shake violently and lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of an engine mount can cause the engine to drop, leading to damage to the transmission, CV joint, and other components, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine mount suddenly fails
pitching the engine and transmission forward and down onto the road
causing the vehicle to lose control and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch fails
causing the gear to slip and move into neutral
making it difficult to shift gears and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of a transmission mount can cause the engine to drop, leading to damage to the transmission, CV joint, and other components, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission mount bolt loosens or breaks
causing the engine to fall out of the engine bay
leading to damage to the transmission
CV joint
and other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mount can cause the engine to fall, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clunking noises
loud bangs
vibrations on the clutch pedal
and difficulty shifting gears. In some cases
the engine may fall or drop
causing damage to surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission mount can cause the transmission to shift improperly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rough shifting
clunking noises
and vibrations on the clutch pedal. In some cases
the transmission may become loose
causing damage to surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose motor mount bolt can cause the engine to fall, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Clunking noises
vibrations on the clutch pedal
and difficulty shifting gears. In some cases
the engine may fall or drop
causing damage to surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension components can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of tire blowout, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Clunking noise coming from the front end of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
tire tread surface making contact with the fender
deep circumferential grooves in the tire
worn-out plastic fender liner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension components can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Clunking sound when going over small bumps
loose and damaged rear wheel stabilizer bolt
rattling noise in the rear of the car
loose anti-roll bar linkage.
